pillars, financial institutions,

00:00:25.780 --> 00:00:28.600
or fis and financial regulators.

00:00:29.080 --> 00:00:31.270
First, let's talk about the fis.

00:00:31.720 --> 00:00:34.180
These are the middlemen
of the money market.

00:00:34.690 --> 00:00:38.620
Imagine them as the great collectors
and distributors of wealth.

00:00:39.129 --> 00:00:43.450
They take funds from people like us
who are saving money, and they channel

00:00:43.450 --> 00:00:45.160
it to those who need to borrow it.

00:00:45.710 --> 00:00:50.000
Be it for a new business, a new
house, or for the government's grand

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:54.560
projects, they are the heroes who
provide services like accepting

00:00:54.560 --> 00:01:00.110
deposits, lending money, managing our
investments, and even offering insurance.

00:01:00.470 --> 00:01:02.360
Your everyday commercial banks.

00:01:02.445 --> 00:01:06.645
Cooperative banks, the famous
non-banking financial companies,

00:01:06.645 --> 00:01:12.105
or mbfc insurance giants and mutual
funds are all part of this family.

00:01:12.555 --> 00:01:17.835
They are absolutely vital for economic
growth because they get idle money moving

00:01:17.955 --> 00:01:20.325
and put capital to work efficiently.

00:01:20.825 --> 00:01:23.015
Now who keeps these money moving?

00:01:23.015 --> 00:01:24.155
Heroes in check.

00:01:24.545 --> 00:01:27.935
Enter the second pillar,
the financial regulators.

00:01:28.355 --> 00:01:31.265
These are the super cops
of the financial world.

00:01:31.655 --> 00:01:35.375
They are government bodies
set up to oversee and control

00:01:35.375 --> 00:01:36.755
what the fis are doing.

00:01:37.190 --> 00:01:41.120
Their main job is to maintain
the stability and integrity

00:01:41.120 --> 00:01:44.780
of the whole system so it
doesn't just collapse one day.

00:01:45.230 --> 00:01:48.410
They protect the interests
of consumers like you and me.

00:01:48.710 --> 00:01:52.940
Prevent financial crimes and make
sure everything is fair and square.

00:01:53.330 --> 00:01:54.005
How do they do this?

00:01:54.675 --> 00:01:58.755
By setting the rules of the game,
giving out licenses, conducting

00:01:58.755 --> 00:02:03.075
surprise inspections, and
enforcing compliance in India.

00:02:03.165 --> 00:02:08.775
Our fantastic four regulators are
the Reserve Bank of India, RBI, the

00:02:08.775 --> 00:02:14.175
Securities and Exchange Board of India
sebi, the Insurance, regulatory and

00:02:14.175 --> 00:02:16.906
Development Authority of India, IRDA.

00:02:17.215 --> 00:02:21.864
And the Pension Fund, regulatory
and Development authority P-F-R-D-A,

00:02:22.285 --> 00:02:23.845
the relationship is simple.

00:02:24.325 --> 00:02:29.875
Fis make the economy run, and regulators
make sure they run safely and ethically,

00:02:30.025 --> 00:02:32.005
building our trust in the system.

00:02:32.475 --> 00:02:34.065
Real world relevance.

